Federal police confirmed Tuesday that a knife attack left one person injured at Düsseldorf Airport. Police said the stabbing took place at a parking ticket vending machine in a parking garage near the departures terminal. The victim was taken to hospital for treatment. The alleged perpetrator is still on the run, with a manhunt underway involving both local and federal police. A police spokesperson said the stabbing resulted from a dispute among homeless people and that there was never any danger to passengers or flight safety. The injuries suffered by the victim were reportedly not severe. tj/rt (Reuters, dpa, AFP) 